The '''Congressional Soccer Match''' is an annual [[association football|soccer]] game played each summer by members of the [[United States Congress]]. The game began in 2013 and in its current format in 2014. In the match, the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republicans]] and [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrats]] form separate teams and play against each other. The event is hosted by the [[United States Soccer Foundation]] and generally features members of the Congressional Soccer Caucus, and former professional players.<ref>{{cite web |title=United legends competing in sixth annual Congressional Soccer Match |url=https://www.dcunited.com/post/2018/05/15/united-legends-competing-sixth-annual-congressional-soccer-match |website=DCUnited.com |accessdate=June 19, 2018}}</ref> The money raised from the match is donated to local charities.<ref>{{cite web |title=Charity soccer match benefiting children living in underserved communities. |url=https://ussoccerfoundation.org/events/congressional-soccer-match |website=U.S. Soccer Foundation}}</ref>

The defending champions are the Democrats.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lora |first1=Maya |title=Dems win nail-biter in charity congressional soccer game |url=http://thehill.com/blogs/in-the-know/388976-dems-win-nail-biter-in-charity-congressional-soccer-game |website=The Hill |accessdate=June 19, 2018 |date=May 23, 2018}}</ref>

