The '''Frontier Service''', also called the '''Committee for State Border Protection of the National Security Service''' and the '''National Border Guard''',<ref>[http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/centralasia/uzbek-army.htm Uzbek Army] Global Security.</ref> is a department of the [[military of Uzbekistan|military]] and [[National Security Service (Uzbekistan)|National Security Service]] of [[Uzbekistan]] responsible for [[border guard|border security]], part of the Security Service since 2005.<ref>[http://registan.net/2013/07/30/rustam-inoyatov-snb-vs-mvd-2/ Rustam Inoyatov: SNB vs MVD] Published 2013. Registran.net.</ref> It has had many disagreements with the [[Kyrgyzstan Frontier Force|Frontier Forces]] of [[Kyrgyzstan]] since 2011.<ref>[http://en.trend.az/regions/casia/kyrgyzstan/1916343.html Uzbekistan's Frontier Service: Kyrgyzstan aggravates situation in Sokh enclave] Published 10 August 2011. Trend.az.</ref>

==Riverine naval force==
A small riverine naval force is operated by the Frontier Service on the [[Amu Darya]] river, with two [[Gurza-class boat|Gurza-class gunboat]]s in service as well as other small craft.<ref>http://www.navyrecognition.com/index.php/news/defence-news/year-2014-news/december-2014-navy-naval-forces-maritime-industry-technology-security-global-news/2293-ukraine-resumed-construction-of-gyurza-m-project-58155-river-armored-artillery-boats.html</ref>

