{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Defence |type = |nativename = Försvarsdepartementet |logo = Försvarsdepartementet vapen.svg |logo_width = 150px |logo_caption = Coat of Arms |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = {{Start date|1920}}<ref name=ne>{{cite encyclopedia | title=Försvarsdepartementet | encyclopedia=[[Nationalencyklopedin]] | language=Swedish | url=http://www.ne.se/försvarsdepartementet | accessdate=13 November 2010}} {{subscription required}}</ref> |preceding1 = |preceding2 = <!-- (etc.) --> |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = |headquarters = |coordinates = |employees = about 150 |budget = |minister1_name = [[Peter Hultqvist]] |minister1_pfo = [[Minister for Defence (Sweden)|Minister for Defence]] <!-- (etc.) --> |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = <!-- (etc.) --> |agency_type = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = <!-- (etc.) --> |keydocument1= <!-- (etc.) --> |website = {{URL|http://www.sweden.gov.se/sb/d/2060}} |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }} {{Politics of Sweden}}
The '''Ministry of Defence''' ({{lang-sv|Försvarsdepartementet}}) is a [[government of Sweden|Swedish government]] [[Ministry (government department)|ministry]] responsible for the national [[Defense (military)|defence]] policy.
The Ministry of Defence has existed in its present form since 1920. It has been located at its present premises at Jakobsgatan 9 at [[Gustav Adolfs torg, Stockholm|Gustaf Adolfs torg]], [[Stockholm]], since 1966. The ministry has a staff of 150: political advisers, officials, assistants, clerical officers, military advisers in military issues, etc. The ministry is headed by the [[Minister for Defence (Sweden)|Minister for Defence]], currently [[Peter Hultqvist]] ([[Social Democrats (Sweden)|s]]).
